title: Weekly Review With Clay and Buck H2 - Jun 11 2022
itunes:title: Weekly Review With Clay and Buck H2 - Jun 11 2022
description:
CNN midterm forecast: GOP's best position in 80 years. Dems prep Jan. 6 prime-time TV show. Buck says: "It's literally theatrics. They're just doing this to try to create spectacle to distract." CDC backtracks on monkeypox mask advisory. Fox News won't air the Democrats' Jan. 6 prime-time show. Clay and Buck say they think Fox will smack down in the ratings all others who are sharing the airing of the "spectacle." Kamala, without going to the border again, goes back to focusing on "root causes" of illegal immigration. C&B say, good idea, Kamala, since that will take only 30 or 40 years most likely to figure out. AOC lectures on using the term "Latinx." C&B bring up the real facts about "Latinx." Did George Washington have a British accent?
